The Ohio State Buckeyes (16-0) will visit the Wisconsin Badgers (10-7) after winning six straight road games.
The Buckeyes are currently heavy 18.5-point favorites over the Badgers. The over/under for the matchup is set at 139.5.

Wisconsin Key Players Serah Williams has the top spot on the Badgers leaderboards for both scoring and rebounding with 18.5 points and 11.2 rebounds per game. Ronnie Porter records more assists than any other Wisconsin player with 4.7 per game. Porter also scores 9.5 points and pulls down 3.9 rebounds per game. Tess Myers averages 1.9 three-pointers per game, the most on the Badgers. Wisconsin's leader in steals is Porter (1.8 per game), and its leader in blocks is Williams (2.8 per game).
